    "summary": "After studying in MAI Bordeaux, I joined a great FMCG company, Reckitt Benckiser, which allowed me to have various experiences over the last years. \nI had the opportunity to join the company as a trainee in the local procurement team of our Polish factory and then global procurement in the Packaging team. \nRather quickly got promoted as Junior Buyer in External Manufacturing for Europe (a great experience as we faced the covid-19 crisis and managed to ensure the increased supply demand with the co-packers.) \nI have recently been promoted to Global Raw Materials Buyer, giving me the opportunity to manage a portfolio with strategic commodities and spend. \n\nProcurement, and supply overall, is a function in which we are directly exposed to environmental/ecological impact of the industry. Sustainability and responsible sourcing should be the priority. We are also directly linked to the net revenue of a company, we must ensure supply and deliver savings. \n\nCurious, mobile, able to manage an important workload and open to opportunities.",
